#!/bin/zsh

# Copy to Config/AppConfig.env for non-secret local helper config only. The
# shipped Android app must not read provider credentials or Maps/Places SDK keys
# from this file.
# User-supplied provider credentials belong in the in-app Settings screen and
# are stored only in encrypted device-local storage after install.
# Android Maps/Places SDK keys belong in local.properties, Gradle properties, or
# environment variables so the app manifest can receive the current build's
# package-restricted key.
